<HEADLINE>
<P>
HERE'S ONE AWARD HE HASN'T WON YET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The NHL season is almost over and people are starting to wonder about 
postseason awards. 
</P>
<P>
According to the latest stats, there is a tie for the coveted Lord Robitussin 
trophy, between Wayne Gretzky and Larry Robinson of the Kings. 
</P>
<P>
The Lord Robitussin, of course, is awarded to the player who coughs up the puck 
the most times during the season. 
</P>
<P>
Good luck to both of you. Either one of you truly deserve it. 
</P>
<P>
STAN PAGE, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
