<HEADLINE>
<P>
REMEMBER TIM RICHMOND AS A GREAT RACE DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Elliott Almond's article, "Family Says Drug Test Falsified," has shed new light 
on the demise of one of NASCAR's bright stars. 
</P>
<P>
Those of us who saw Tim Richmond race know that he had attained the driver's 
goal of being a part of the car. 
</P>
<P>
Unfortunately, we will read of many more sports figures who will be maligned by 
bogus drug-testing procedures and those that will perish from AIDS. 
</P>
<P>
T.L. COLEMAN SR., San Bernardino 
</P>
