<HEADLINE>
<P>
IF SEASON IS LONGER, IT SHOULD BE BETTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As long as the NFL is going to revise its schedule to 17 weeks, they should 
take the opportunity to make it more fair and competitive: 
</P>
<P>
(1) All teams should play weeks 1-5 and 13-17, with all byes to occur in weeks 
6-12 (four teams a week for seven weeks). 
</P>
<P>
(2) Weeks 14-17 should be reserved for intradivision play. 
</P>
<P>
(3) No "Monday Night Football" in the last week of the season. All teams should 
get the same amount of rest before the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
JAMES OLMSTEAD, Valencia 
</P>
</TEXT>
