<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
STICH WINS, FACES MULLER IN MEMPHIS SEMIFINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michael Stich advanced to the semifinal round of the Volvo Indoor tennis 
tournament with a 6-4, 7-6 (7-5) victory over Malivai Washington Friday night 
at Memphis, Tenn. 
</P>
<P>
Stich, ranked 80th in the world, eliminated Andrei Chesnokov, the tournament's 
third-seeded player, in the third round. 
</P>
<P>
The West German will meet South Africa's Gary Muller, a 7-5, 7-5 winner over 
Danie Visser, in today's semifinals. Muller upset top-seeded Stefan Edberg in 
the second round. 
</P>
<P>
In the other semifinal, Glenn Layendecker, who beat Finland's Veli Paloheimo, 
5-7, 7-6 (7-3), 6-4, in a three-hour marathon, will meet sixth-seeded Wally 
Masur of Australia, who beat No. 13 Petr Korda of Czechoslovakia, 6-4, 7-5. 
</P>
<P>
Layendecker earlier upset No. 2 seeded Michael Chang. 
</P>
<P>
Emilio Sanchez of Spain beat Pete Sampras, 6-3, 2-6, 6-1, to improve to 2-0 in 
the round-robin Eagle tournament at Scottsdale, Ariz. Andre Agassi defeated Tim 
Mayotte, 2-6, 6-3, 6-2, which gave both a 1-1 record. 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Brad Gilbert defeated Amos Mansdorf of Israel, 6-1, 7-6 (8-6), and 
Michael Tauson of Denmark upset fifth-seeded Magnus Gustafsson of Sweden, 6-3, 
1-6, 7-6 (7-4), to reach the semifinals of the ABN World tournament at 
Rotterdam, the Netherlands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
