<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION BOYS ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JIM COLEMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Faith Baptist 65, Brethern 59 -- The Contenders became Southern Section 1-A 
Division champions after their overtime victory over Brethren at Biola 
University. 
</P>
<P>
Faith Baptist (19-10) won despite making one field goal in the fourth quarter 
and being outscored, 12-6, in the final 3:32. 
</P>
<P>
Alex Estrada scored 11 of his game-high 26 points in the third quarter to help 
increase Faith Baptist's 29-24 lead to 45-35. 
</P>
<P>
But Chris Beck tied the game, 55-55, with two free throws with 28 seconds left 
in regulation. 
</P>
<P>
Brethren finished 19-9. JIM COLEMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
