<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION BOYS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
RIBET CHRISTIAN, FAITH BAPTIST ARE VICTORIOUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
La Canada Ribet Christian Academy won its first boys Small Schools Division 
basketball title Friday night in an unorthodox fashion. 
</P>
<P>
The Fighting Frogs had to put up a fight. 
</P>
<P>
Jamel Duncan scored seven of his 19 points during an 11-2 third-quarter run in 
pushing Ribet to a 68-60 victory over San Juan Capistrano's St. Margaret's, 
68-60, before 800 at Saddleback College in Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
It was the 20th consecutive victory for the Fighting Frogs (25-2), who 
outscored their opponents by an average of 47 points in their first four 
playoff games. 
</P>
<P>
St. Margaret's is 21-4. MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
