<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUPER MATH TEACHER JAIME ESCALANTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am not surprised that Escalante has decided to quit public school teaching. 
</P>
<P>
Escalante's success in teaching an academic discipline is an aberration in a 
school system that lobotomizes its students. 
</P>
<P>
In fact, those who begrudge his success would have offered him unconditional 
love, moral support and admiration had he been a championship football coach, 
the sponsor of a massive fund-raiser or one of the countless mindless, 
frivolous non-academic extracurricular frills that abound on the campus of 
every school, college and university throughout the nation. 
</P>
<P>
Teachers who ask for academic reforms must be punished! Five years ago a former 
principal took away the French classes she knew I loved to teach, and last 
summer I was blacklisted when I applied for a French teaching position in 
another school. 
</P>
<P>
Our public schools will never improve until anti-academic administrators are 
replaced with those who will reward dedicated, brilliant, hard-working and 
gifted teachers like Escalante, instead of kicking them out of the school 
system! 
</P>
<P>
GILBERT A. RUBIO 
</P>
<P>
La Puente 
</P>
