</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA030390-0032 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 183994 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 3, 1990, Saturday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 7; Column 1; Letters Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
147 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
REAGAN'S TAPED TESTIMONY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Incredible, isn't it? For eight years we had a President who knew nothing, did 
not want to know anything, had his wishes carried out by underlings with the 
unspoken directive to be told nothing -- to keep him the hell out of whatever 
was going on -- and we loved him for it, and seemingly still do. 
</P>
<P>
We prate and boast to the rest of the world of our beautiful democracy and 
suggest that it be emulated by one and all. 
</P>
<P>
Just who are we kidding? We are a bunch of idiots, nothing less, for knowing 
and putting up with this charade and reelecting him by an overwhelming 
majority, really knowing deep inside that he did not, could not cope with the 
immensity of his position and we laughed at it all. 
</P>
<P>
Are we still laughing? One wonders. Is there any limit to the gullibility and 
stupidity which we are still able to generate. 
</P>
<P>
Heaven help us all. 
</P>
<P>
JACK CHESNER 
</P>
<P>
North Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
