<HEADLINE>
<P>
REAGAN'S TAPED TESTIMONY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I wonder if we would be dragging ourselves through the murky waters of the 
Iran-Contra troubles if that bizarre scheme had been a success and all the 
hostages had been brought home. 
</P>
<P>
I also wonder if Reagan's detractors might be a little more charitable and 
think of him not in terms of that failure, but as the American President who 
walked through Red Square with Mikhail Gorbachev -- and quite possibly changed 
the political climate of the world in so doing. 
</P>
<P>
TONY THOMAS 
</P>
<P>
Burbank 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
