<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF : FIFTH MEMBER NAMED TO RENT CONTROL BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The deadlock over the appointment of the fifth member to the Santa Monica Rent 
Control Board, which had threatened to indefinitely hamper board business, was 
broken Thursday night with the selection of Jay P. Johnson, 47, an apartment 
owner who supports rent control. 
</P>
<P>
Board member Eileen Lipson, who had sided with board member Dolores Press in 
the deadlock against board Chairwoman Susan Packer Davis and board member Wayne 
Bauer, said she swung her vote because she thinks Johnson is open-minded and "a 
person of great integrity." 
</P>
<P>
The board had been trying since Jan. 22 to agree on a replacement for Julie 
Lopez Dad, who resigned late last year. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson's appointment comes at a time when the city's rent control ordinance, 
considered among the toughest in the nation, is under attack by landlords. 
</P>
</TEXT>
