Roddy, 60, a retired telephone company worker, said she would not be 
intimidated by threats. 
</P>
<P>
Roddy narrowly escaped injury New Year's Eve when two suspected dealers stood 
across the street from her stucco house and opened fire with semiautomatic 
weapons. Bullets grazed Roddy's abdomen and punched holes in walls, windows and 
furniture. 
