<P>
THATCHER POPULARITY LOWEST IN 19 YEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The political fortunes of British Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher have plunged 
further with the release of an opinion poll showing her Conservative Party 
18.5% behind the opposition Labor Party, its lowest standing in 19 years. The 
survey undertaken by Gallup for the Daily Telegraph newspaper indicated 
Thatcher's slide is due to a controversial new tax and her refusal to lower 
interest rates to spur economic growth. The poll put the Labor Party of Neil 
Kinnock at 49.5%, a rise of 1.5% from two previous polls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
