<P>
LEBANON; 
</P>
<P>
AOUN PULLS BACK AFTER CLERIC'S THREAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Maj. Gen. Michel Aoun's troops gave up some ground gained in the latest savage 
fighting with the Lebanese Forces militia as part of a withdrawal apparently 
prompted by church and international pressure. The troops withdrew shortly 
after Lebanese Maronite Patriarch Nasrallah Butros Sfeir threatened Christian 
warlords and their men with excommunication unless they halted their month-old 
war for control of Christian East Beirut. Both Aoun and Lebanese Forces leader 
Samir Geagea vowed in separate statements to abide by the cease-fire called for 
by Sfeir. 
</P>
