<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
PERU; 
</P>
<P>
PEASANTS DECAPITATE 9 MAOIST GUERRILLAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Outraged highland peasants armed with sickles and homemade shotguns captured 13 
Sendero Luminoso (Shining Path) guerrillas, killed them and sent the heads of 
nine of them to the local army commander, police said. Police said 200 peasants 
who organized into a village defense group because of their fear of reprisal by 
the Maoist-inspired insurgents ambushed 20 of them near Cochas, a town 30 miles 
northeast of Huancayo. After capturing the better-armed but outnumbered rebels, 
the peasants decapitated the nine. 
</P>
