</P>
<P>
NEW YORK; 
</P>
<P>
EXXON HALTS BARGES, TANKERS AFTER SPILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Exxon Corp. suspended all tanker and barge operations at its massive Bayway 
Refinery and Bayonne Terminal pending an investigation into the second major 
oil spill in three months in a busy waterway separating New York and New 
Jersey. Cleanup crews finished mopping up a spill of 3,500 gallons of heavy oil 
into the Arthur Kill waterway, and Capt. Robert North, Coast Guard captain of 
the Port of New York, reported there was "no free-floating oil seen anywhere in 
the harbor or in Arthur Kill." 
</P>
