<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO-DEMOCRACY STRIKE CLOSES NEPAL CAPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KATMANDU, Nepal 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A general strike called by Nepal's banned political parties to back their 
campaign for multi-party democracy virtually shut down Katmandu on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Political parties, outlawed 30 years ago as the country moved to a partyless 
system of elected councils, had appealed for a peaceful strike in the capital 
and towns across the Himalayan kingdom. Only a few violent incidents were 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
The government of absolute monarch King Birendra, 44, has shown no signs of 
willingness to alter Nepal's political system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
