<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; 
</P>
<P>
DORNAN WON'T SEEK REELECTION TO COUNCIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Irvine City Councilman Ed Dornan announced this week that he will not seek 
reelection when his term is up in June so that he can write books and conduct 
research abroad. 
</P>
<P>
Dornan, 50, an English teacher at Orange Coast College, said he had to decide 
whether or not to more fully pursue his professional life. 
</P>
<P>
"It's a matter of choosing what I want to do," Dornan said. 
</P>
<P>
He added that during an upcoming year on academic leave, he plans to do 
research in France and Italy as well as on the East Coast. He said he is also 
about to finish a textbook and is working on a novel. 
</P>
<P>
Elected in 1986, Dornan is considered an ally of Irvine Mayor Larry Agran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
