<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; 
</P>
<P>
REOPENING PLANNED OF 2 HIGHWAY LANES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES M. GOMEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City officials announced Friday that a stretch of coastal highway will be 
reopened in two weeks, but the roadway will not be fully accessible until July 
1. 
</P>
<P>
Two lanes of El Camino Real between Camino Capistrano and Avenida Pico will be 
opened while crews work to shore up the 1,800-foot-long cliff that runs 
adjacent to the highway, according to City Manager Michael Parness. 
</P>
<P>
The roadway has been closed since Feb. 6. 
</P>
<P>
A bike path, also closed since then, will also be reopened. 
</P>
<P>
Closure of the road has caused traffic problems and complaints from a handful 
of business owners who say that customers can no longer reach their stores. 
</P>
<P>
The two lanes that will be opened to relieve traffic congestion will close 
again in April while crews haul away up to 200,000 cubic yards of dirt from the 
site. 
</P>
<P>
The two lanes will then reopen May 15, Parness said, and remain open through 
July. JAMES M. GOMEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
