<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHWARTZ HEADS SPEEDWAY FIELD AT LONG BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bobby Schwartz, the defending U.S. speedway motorcycle champion, heads a field 
of 20 riders scheduled to compete in the opening race of the Spring Series at 8 
tonight at Long Beach Veterans Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Schwartz, of Costa Mesa, has won the series the past three years. He is 
expected to challenged by Billy Hamill of Monrovia and veteran overseas riders 
Ricky Miller, Lance King and Gary Hicks. 
</P>
<P>
The event features five-man scratch heat races. 
</P>
<P>
The series resumes March 9 at the Orange County Fairgrounds. The season opener 
of weekly racing at the Costa Mesa track is scheduled March 30. 
</P>
