<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE STATE WOMEN'S BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
THIS TIME, GOLDEN WEST REACHES FINAL GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRENDAN HEALEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
VISALIA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Golden West College made up for a slow start in plenty of time to take a 74-59 
victory over Cerritos in the semifinals of state tournament Friday night at 
College of the Sequoias. 
</P>
<P>
Golden West scored only 10 points in the first 10 minutes, but point guard Bits 
Sirchia broke free for 12 points in the next 10 to spark the Rustlers. 
</P>
<P>
Sirchia and Claudette Jackson led Golden West with 18 points each. 
</P>
<P>
Golden West (36-1) will play College of the Sequoias at 7 tonight for the state 
championship. 
</P>
<P>
Golden West has made the state tournament the past four years, but this is the 
first time the Rustlers have reached the championship game. 
</P>
<P>
"Bits Sirchia saved us in the first half," Golden West Coach Dave Stricklin 
said. "Every time the ball went inside, they sagged off. . . . Once she hit 
those, they didn't sag as much." 
</P>
<P>
Cerritos (26-7) slowed the game and built a 16-10 lead, but Golden West led, 
34-25, at the half and padded the margin with a 16-2 run to start the second 
half. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson grabbed 14 rebounds as did Donna Gondringer, who continued to struggle 
offensively with nine points. 
</P>
<P>
Dawn Haag came off the bench to score eight consecutive points for Golden West. 
She finished with 10. 
</P>
<P>
Cerritos' Lisa Pounds made six three-point shots and scored 22. BRENDAN HEALEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
