<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RETAIL/TOURISM; 
</P>
<P>
CALIFORNIA'S SECOND RIPLEY'S MUSEUM DUE IN BUENA PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Thuan Le Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Francisco may still be the only place in California with a Bay Bridge, but 
Orange County is about to follow San Francisco's lead and become the state's 
second site of a Ripley's Believe It Or Not Museum. 
</P>
<P>
Fong &amp; Paul Associates, operator of the Movieland Wax Museum on Beach 
Boulevard, has acquired a franchise from Ripley International Inc., in Toronto, 
Canada, and plans to open for business in Buena Park in June. 
</P>
<P>
The operators will invest about $250,000 to set up the museum, said marketing 
director Barry Muszik. 
</P>
<P>
Fong &amp; Paul has retained Irvine's Jordan-Valli Architects Inc. to develop 
an 8,500-square-foot facility across the street from Movieland. 
</P>
<P>
There are 13 Ripley's museums worldwide and five more are being planned, 
including one each in Japan and Europe, Muszik said. 
</P>
<P>
Ron Fong, president of Fong &amp; Paul Associates, said he is searching for 
more Hollywood memorabilia to be featured in a special area at the Orange 
County Ripley's. In addition to the Hollywood collection, the museum will 
showcase cultural, political and scientific oddities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
